  "prompt": "How can I open PayPal without a bank account?",
  "response": "You can open a PayPal account without linking it to a bank account by following these steps:\n\n1. **Sign Up**: Go to the PayPal website or download the PayPal app and click on \"Sign Up.\"\n2. **Choose Account Type**: Select either a Personal or Business account, depending on your needs.\n3. **Provide Basic Information**: Fill in your personal information, such as your name, email address, and a secure password.\n4. **Verify Your Email**: PayPal will send a verification email to the address you provided. Click on the link in that email to verify your email address.\n5. **Complete Profile**: Provide additional information as requested, such as your address and phone number.\n\nYou can use PayPal for transactions (sending and receiving money) without a bank account in a few ways:\n\n1. **Credit/Debit Card**: Link a credit or debit card to your PayPal account for funding purposes. This allows you to make payments and purchases through PayPal without needing a bank account.\n2. **Send/Receive Payments**: You can still receive payments or money from others into your PayPal balance.\n\nHowever, keep in mind that some features of PayPal may be limited without a bank account. For example, withdrawing funds from your PayPal balance usually requires linking a bank account.",
